  "description": "A lighter evening recipe designed to feel comforting without becoming heavy or starch-dense. Adai with Avial brings a distinct structure, seasoning pattern, and grain-legume balance to the table.",
  "preparation": "",
  "cooking_steps": [
    "Heat a tawa on medium heat and spread 130 ml batter into a thick round.",
    "Drizzle oil around the edge and cook 3 minutes until the underside browns and the top loses its raw sheen.",
    "Flip and cook 2 more minutes on medium-low heat until the center is cooked through.",
    "Serve hot with light avial."
  ],
